commentary: Wood to Azhar Ali, OUT an appeal for caught behind, not given by umpire Fry. YJB almost immediately signals for a review. Suggests there was some bat there.There was a noise as the ball ran past the bat, and snicko detects a spike. Azhar has to exit. Two wickets in three balls for Wood! Banged in short and outside off, Azhar was caught between pulling and leaving. He does a bit of this and a bit of that. Looks highly ungainly. Grazes the top edge (a very thin one) and settles into the gloves of YJB

text: an appeal for caught behind, not given by umpire Fry. YJB almost immediately signals for a review. commentary: Dawson to Sarfraz Ahmed, OUT Dawson holds his nerve and strikes on ODI debut. Mid-on was in the circle. Sarfraz does not shy away from a challenge. He charges at the left-arm spinning allrounder and goes against the spin. Quicker than the previous delivery, instead of lofting it, he ends up dragging it in the air. Hales judges it superbly. He runs back and takes it over his head. Sarfraz signs off as the leading run-getter in the series. Well done
shortText: Dawson to Sarfraz Ahmed, OUT
text: Dawson holds his nerve and strikes on ODI debut. Mid-on was in the circle. Sarfraz does not shy away from a challenge. He charges at the left-arm spinning allrounder and goes against the spin. Quicker than the previous delivery, instead of lofting it, he ends up dragging it in the air. Hales judges it superbly. He runs back and takes it over his head. Sarfraz signs off as the leading run-getter in the series. Well done
